Beijing Document Service(BDS) is a new-type information service providing online information retrieval service mainly in Beijing and other cities besides. This paper presents the background, goals, design considerations of the BDS system and what have been done in achieving the goal of loading the NTIS Bibliographic Data Base into the system and providing its online service to the public. System appraisal is covered and in light of problems experienced by BDS, possible approaches of how modernized information retrieval systems might be developed in China are also discussed.